# The published npm tarball is dist/ only — enforced by `files: ["dist"]` in package.json, which is an
# allowlist and the primary guard. This denylist is belt-and-suspenders: it keeps heavy media and source
# out of the package even if `files` is ever loosened. npm always includes package.json, README.md, and
# LICENSE regardless of this file.

# Heavy media — README badges & logos (~1 MB of JPG/PNG). Rendered from GitHub; never needed once installed.
assets/
.tui-preview/

# Source & tooling — the package ships compiled dist/, not the TypeScript source or dev configs.
src/
scripts/
docs/
examples/
.github/
.husky/
tsconfig*.json
eslint.config.js
vitest.config.*

# Local notes & generated noise.
CONTEXT.md
language.md
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
llms.txt
*.log
*.tsbuildinfo
